init_text: Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: they say, as they grab a towel.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "We'll just get it off you, and then you can go back to your party."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "No, no, no, I can't be near it!" I scream.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Oh, thank you, thank you, I can't believe you got it off me."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I say, as I run back to the party.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "You're welcome, Your Majesty", the maid says, as she turns to go back to the party.

actions.name: text-delete
actions.text: "You're welcome, Your Majesty", the maid says, as she turns to go back to the party.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "That was weird", I hear the maid say.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I've never seen someone react like that to a bee before."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I'm not surprised", the other maid says.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "She's always been a bit of a weirdo."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I heard that too", the first maid says.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I run back to the deck, and grab the first maid by the hair.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "How dare you talk about me like that!"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I scream, as I pull her to the ground.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I am the queen, and you will show me respect!"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I'm sorry, Your Majesty", the maid says, as she tries to get up.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I kick her in the stomach, and she falls back to the ground.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I'm sorry, I'm sorry, I'm sorry!" she screams.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I'm not done with you yet", I say, as I grab her by the neck.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "You will never disrespect me again, or I will have you executed."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I let go of her, and she crawls away.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Now, I'm going back to my party."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I walk back to the party, and the guests are all staring at me.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I was just teaching a servant a lesson."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I think you should go back to your room", my husband says.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I'm just going to go get a drink."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I walk over to the bar, and the bartender hands me a drink.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I take a sip, and I feel a wave of calm wash over me.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I feel so much better, so much more relaxed.
